      "comment": "MAJOR HAYLEY (4) has been racing well of late and looks close to a win after placing in three of her last four starts. Drew on the back row at this circuit and distance at her latest appearance but found the front and boxed on for third, beaten 1.4 metres. Could break through. SHOOBEES LOU (1) hasn't raced since winning at Leeton in October but has been trialling well and gets the ace draw. Has upside so looking for a strong return. ALWAYSTHEWILDEST (6) looks a filly of some promise having scored by 3 metres at this venue at her first career run last week. Draws wider but has upside. FEELGOOD RAY (10) came from a similar barrier to this to win at Junee last month and could be close to another success following back-to-back seconds.",
